# What must not be uploaded to Function Compute.
#
# `code: ../` in deploy/s.yaml points at the repo root, so without this file the bundle would carry
# the virtualenv, the git history, the eval dataset and every report - hundreds of megabytes of
# things the function will never import. FC has an upload size limit, and even under it, a fat
# bundle is a slow cold start on every single request.

.venv/
venv/
.git/
.github/
.mypy_cache/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.coverage*
htmlcov/

# The eval dataset and its reports are evidence, not runtime. The deployed function never reads them.
eval/
tests/
docs/
node_modules/

# NOT excluded: src/quotemind/web/. The dashboard used to live in a top-level web/ directory and this
# file excluded it - correctly, when it was uploaded to OSS separately. It is now served by the API
# (TASK-106), so it must travel in the bundle, and a bare `web/` pattern here would match it at any
# depth and strip it right back out. The dashboard would 500 on a missing file, in production only.

# Never ship secrets into a function bundle - the values arrive as environment variables instead.
.env
.env.*
